========================================================================
PART 2: NIST ELAS3D (CORE SOLVER)
========================================================================
The core finite element solver in this repository is a derivative work of the 
software described in NIST Interagency/Internal Report (NISTIR) 6269.

Original Source: 
   Garboczi, E. (1998), "Finite Element and Finite Difference Programs for 
   Computing the Linear Electric and Elastic Properties of Digital Images 
   of Random Materials."

Status: 
   Public Domain (17 U.S.C. ยง 105) - Works of the U.S. Federal Government.

